 P(m,\lambda,\mu)= \frac{\mu^m e^{-\lambda}}{m!} \sum_{j=m}^{\infty} \frac{\lambda^j(1-\mu)^{j-m}}{(j-m)!} 
 P(m,\lambda,\mu)= \frac{\mu^m e^{-\lambda}}{m!} \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{\lambda^{n+m}(1-\mu)^{n}}{n!} 
